page.title: 15PLANTS ON GOG MAGOG HILLS
page.content:
{ PLANTS } There are 200+ flowering plants and many grasses on 54 acres studied.
{ RARE } Unusual species for the area include the marsh plants Yellow Pimpernel and Hemp Agrimony. Also nationally rare Ajuga Genevensis.The Cowslip, previously endangered, is now grown by warden at Wandlebury. Rare White Honeysuckle in wooded area.
{ POISONOUS } These include Deadly, Black and Woody Nightshades. { { WOODLAND FLORA } White/Blue Bluebells, 15 species of Daffodils (including Pure White Head), Honeysuckle, Christmas Rose, Aconites, Primroses and Cowslips.
